"{\"uid\": \"abc7ny.com-post-paris-olympics-image-surfer-apparently-defies-gravity-15121985\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"It was a celebration worthy of the ages - or at least viral fame.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 65, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a celebration\", \"from\": 7, \"to\": 20}, {\"ngram\": \"the ages\", \"from\": 31, \"to\": 39}, {\"ngram\": \"at least viral fame\", \"from\": 45, \"to\": 64}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Surfer Gabriel Medina was taking on Kanoa Igarashi, the man who beat him at the Tokyo Olympics and eventually won silver, and he was looking to turn the tide this time around.\", \"from\": 67, \"to\": 242, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 74, \"end\": 88, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Medina\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gabriel Medina\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Medina\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Medina\"}, {\"begin\": 103, \"end\": 117, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kanoa_Igarashi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kanoa Igarashi\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kanoa_Igarashi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kanoa_Igarashi\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the man\", \"from\": 119, \"to\": 126}, {\"ngram\": \"the Tokyo Olympics\", \"from\": 143, \"to\": 161}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 181, \"to\": 187}, {\"ngram\": \"the tide\", \"from\": 216, \"to\": 224}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Brazilian not only managed to take down the Japanese surfer, he did so in part thanks to a near-perfect 9.90-scoring wave on Day 3 of the surfing competition in Tahiti - taking part halfway around the world from Paris.\", \"from\": 244, \"to\": 466, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 292, \"end\": 300, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\", \"score\": 0.9723873369404027, \"rank\": 0.027277395370530803, \"text\": \"Japanese\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\"}, {\"begin\": 409, \"end\": 415, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 0.9999779152125399, \"rank\": 2.2080686668493972e-05, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}, {\"begin\": 460, \"end\": 465, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999997842224, \"rank\": 2.1581421804462908e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Brazilian\", \"from\": 244, \"to\": 257}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 322, \"to\": 326}, {\"ngram\": \"a near-perfect 9.90-scoring wave\", \"from\": 337, \"to\": 369}, {\"ngram\": \"Day\", \"from\": 373, \"to\": 376}, {\"ngram\": \"the surfing competition\", \"from\": 382, \"to\": 405}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 445, \"to\": 454}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was the highest-scoring wave in Olympic history.\", \"from\": 467, \"to\": 518, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the highest-scoring wave\", \"from\": 474, \"to\": 498}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic history\", \"from\": 502, \"to\": 517}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The resultant jubilation produced another moment of perfection: Medina leapt from his surfboard, raised his finger aloft and his board just managed to fly parallel to him as photographer Jerome Brouillet from Agence France-Presse snapped the shot.\", \"from\": 520, \"to\": 767, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 584, \"end\": 590, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Medina\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.9425987079498877e-16, \"text\": \"Medina\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Medina\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Medina\"}, {\"begin\": 707, \"end\": 713, \"t